---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About | Boho Digital"
  description="Boho Digital is a forest-inspired SEO and digital marketing studio built around clarity, documentation, and better ownership."
  image="/assets/backgrounds/forest-mist.webp"
>
  <section class="page-hero section-forest image-backed">
    <div class="container page-hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-panel" data-reveal>
        <div class="breadcrumbs">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <strong>About</strong>
        </div>
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>A modern forest studio for growth work that stays readable.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Boho Digital combines SEO, content, website optimization, analytics, and
          provider-transfer support with a bias toward ownership clarity and durable
          documentation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-side-panel" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="micro-label">What matters here</p>
        <ul class="ledger-list">
          <li>Readable strategy instead of agency fog</li>
          <li>Search systems that leave a useful trail</li>
          <li>Careful language around climate and AI</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container chapter-grid">
      <article class="section-card" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">Philosophy</p>
        <p>
          A website should feel like a clear environment, not a pile of disconnected
          tasks. Search, content, reporting, and ownership are part of the same system.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="section-card" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="eyebrow">Practice</p>
        <p>
          Boho favors smaller useful systems, careful documentation, and work that
          remains understandable after the launch glow wears off.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
